# Jesse Dodge | Semantic Scholar

[

## BLOOM: A 176B-Parameter Open-Access Multilingual Language Model

](/paper/BLOOM%3A-A-176B-Parameter-Open-Access-Multilingual-Scao-Fan/964bd39b546f0f6625ff3b9ef1083f797807ef2e)

[Teven Le Scao](/author/Teven-Le-Scao/1379806208)[Angela Fan](/author/Angela-Fan/144270981) [Thomas Wolf](/author/Thomas-Wolf/50335211)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   9 November 2022

BLOOM is a 176B-parameter open-access language model designed and built thanks to a collaboration of hundreds of researchers and achieves competitive performance on a wide variety of benchmarks, with stronger results after undergoing multitask prompted finetuning.

## Key-Value Memory Networks for Directly Reading Documents

](/paper/Key-Value-Memory-Networks-for-Directly-Reading-Miller-Fisch/bba5f2852b1db8a18004eb7328efa5e1d57cc62a)

[Alexander H. Miller](/author/Alexander-H.-Miller/143622869)[Adam Fisch](/author/Adam-Fisch/2064150446)[Jesse Dodge](/author/Jesse-Dodge/34176020)[Amir-Hossein Karimi](/author/Amir-Hossein-Karimi/145926563)[Antoine Bordes](/author/Antoine-Bordes/1713934)[J. Weston](/author/J.-Weston/145183709)

Computer Science

-   9 June 2016

This work introduces a new method, Key-Value Memory Networks, that makes reading documents more viable by utilizing different encodings in the addressing and output stages of the memory read operation.

[

## Green AI

](/paper/Green-AI-Schwartz-Dodge/3c5f1ab37f70db503636075e15b3173f86eea00b)

[Roy Schwartz](/author/Roy-Schwartz/4671928)[Jesse Dodge](/author/Jesse-Dodge/34176020)[Noah A. Smith](/author/Noah-A.-Smith/144365875)[Oren Etzioni](/author/Oren-Etzioni/1741101)

Environmental Science, Computer Science

-   22 July 2019

The goal is to make AI both greener and more inclusive---enabling any inspired undergraduate with a laptop to write high-quality research papers and reporting the financial cost or"price tag" of developing, training, and running models to provide baselines for the investigation of increasingly efficient methods.

[

## OLMo: Accelerating the Science of Language Models

](/paper/OLMo%3A-Accelerating-the-Science-of-Language-Models-Groeneveld-Beltagy/ac45bbf9940512d9d686cf8cd3a95969bc313570)

[Dirk Groeneveld](/author/Dirk-Groeneveld/3458736)[Iz Beltagy](/author/Iz-Beltagy/2260133345) [Hanna Hajishirzi](/author/Hanna-Hajishirzi/2264251662)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   1 February 2024

OLMo is built, a competitive, truly Open Language Model, to enable the scientific study of language models and it is hoped this release will empower the open research community and inspire a new wave of innovation.

[

## Fine-Tuning Pretrained Language Models: Weight Initializations, Data Orders, and Early Stopping

](/paper/Fine-Tuning-Pretrained-Language-Models%3A-Weight-Data-Dodge-Ilharco/baf60d13c98916b77b09bc525ede1cd610ed1db5)

[Jesse Dodge](/author/Jesse-Dodge/34176020)[Gabriel Ilharco](/author/Gabriel-Ilharco/2123694087)[Roy Schwartz](/author/Roy-Schwartz/4671928)[Ali Farhadi](/author/Ali-Farhadi/143787583)[Hannaneh Hajishirzi](/author/Hannaneh-Hajishirzi/2548384)[Noah A. Smith](/author/Noah-A.-Smith/144365875)

Computer Science

-   15 February 2020

This work investigates how the performance of the best-found model varies as a function of the number of fine-tuning trials, and examines two factors influenced by the choice of random seed: weight initialization and training data order.

[

## Documenting Large Webtext Corpora: A Case Study on the Colossal Clean Crawled Corpus

](/paper/Documenting-Large-Webtext-Corpora%3A-A-Case-Study-on-Dodge-Marasovic/1adadbfa95e43a70fcd17e6ce947a0652b86bfc3)

[Jesse Dodge](/author/Jesse-Dodge/34176020)[Ana Marasovic](/author/Ana-Marasovic/2127450728)[Gabriel Ilharco](/author/Gabriel-Ilharco/2123694087)[Dirk Groeneveld](/author/Dirk-Groeneveld/3458736)[Margaret Mitchell](/author/Margaret-Mitchell/49501003)[Matt Gardner](/author/Matt-Gardner/40642935)

Computer Science

-   18 April 2021

This work provides some of the first documentation for the Colossal Clean Crawled Corpus (C4), a dataset created by applying a set of filters to a single snapshot of Common Crawl, and evaluates the text that was removed, and shows that blocklist filtering disproportionately removes text from and about minority individuals.

[

## Multimodal C4: An Open, Billion-scale Corpus of Images Interleaved With Text

](/paper/Multimodal-C4%3A-An-Open%2C-Billion-scale-Corpus-of-Zhu-Hessel/df958800014d310b6df34ad83d771314d68fbb2d)

[Wanrong Zhu](/author/Wanrong-Zhu/51439692)[Jack Hessel](/author/Jack-Hessel/2689239) [Yejin Choi](/author/Yejin-Choi/1699545)

Computer Science

-   14 April 2023

This work releases Multimodal C4, an augmentation of the popular text-only C4 corpus with images interleaved, and uses a linear assignment algorithm to place images into longer bodies of text using CLIP features, a process that shows outperforms alternatives.

[

## The Right Tool for the Job: Matching Model and Instance Complexities

](/paper/The-Right-Tool-for-the-Job%3A-Matching-Model-and-Schwartz-Stanovsky/c5cc2340766d68ece08bb1520d357bcf8c03ad48)

[Roy Schwartz](/author/Roy-Schwartz/4671928)[Gabriel Stanovsky](/author/Gabriel-Stanovsky/2157025)[Swabha Swayamdipta](/author/Swabha-Swayamdipta/2705113)[Jesse Dodge](/author/Jesse-Dodge/34176020)[Noah A. Smith](/author/Noah-A.-Smith/144365875)

Computer Science

-   16 April 2020

This work proposes a modification to contextual representation fine-tuning which allows for an early (and fast) “exit” from neural network calculations for simple instances, and late (and accurate) exit for hard instances during inference.

[

## Dolma: an Open Corpus of Three Trillion Tokens for Language Model Pretraining Research

](/paper/Dolma%3A-an-Open-Corpus-of-Three-Trillion-Tokens-for-Soldaini-Kinney/ad1bb59e3e18a0dd8503c3961d6074f162baf710)

[Luca Soldaini](/author/Luca-Soldaini/3328733)[Rodney Kinney](/author/Rodney-Kinney/2282136328) [Kyle Lo](/author/Kyle-Lo/46258841)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   31 January 2024

To facilitate scientific research on language model pretraining, Dolma is curate and released, a three-trillion-token English corpus built from a diverse mixture of web content, scientific papers, code, public-domain books, social media, and encyclopedic materials.

[

## Midge: Generating Image Descriptions From Computer Vision Detections

](/paper/Midge%3A-Generating-Image-Descriptions-From-Computer-Mitchell-Dodge/355de7460120ddc1150d9ce3756f9848983f7ff4)

[Margaret Mitchell](/author/Margaret-Mitchell/49501003)[Jesse Dodge](/author/Jesse-Dodge/34176020) [Hal Daumé](/author/Hal-Daum%C3%A9/1722360)

Computer Science

-   23 April 2012

A novel generation system that composes humanlike descriptions of images from computer vision detections by leveraging syntactically informed word co-occurrence statistics and automatically generating some of the most natural image descriptions to date.
